Introductory microeconomics.  How individuals and firms behave, and why we need a government.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to introduce the students to the main concepts and results of microeconomics, and the way how economists think.The course provides an in depth coverage of Microeconomics and is focused on Consumer Demand, Producer Behavior, Market Structure and Strategic Behavior, and General Equilibrium.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the subject:
- understands the assumptions and logic behind the economic thinking (formal economic models)
- can describe many everyday problems as theoretical microeconomic models; 
- can analyze standard situations using microeconomic reasoning;
- can apply either verbal, graphic or mathematical models;
- has experience using formal models for analyzing real life problems;
- can critically assess the practical application possibilities of such a model;
